<font face="Comic Sans MS">A leave of absence is all.
An indefinite leave of absence.</font>

188
00:25:51,648 --> 00:25:53,190
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- You are firing me.
- During which ...</font>

189
00:25:53,275 --> 00:25:56,110
<font face="Comic Sans MS">they've agreed to continue to pay
your full salary for a period ...</font>

190
00:25:56,194 --> 00:25:57,653
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I don't want their money!</font>

191
00:25:57,737 --> 00:26:00,239
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Please don't be foolish.</font>

192
00:26:00,323 --> 00:26:02,241
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You don't know what I had to go
through to get that for you.</font>

193
00:26:02,325 --> 00:26:05,578
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You went through? What exactly
did you have to go through, Charlie?</font>

194
00:26:05,662 --> 00:26:07,037
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Henry ...</font>

195
00:26:09,165 --> 00:26:11,041
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I resigned.</font>

196
00:26:18,758 --> 00:26:20,426
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Where will you go?</font>

197
00:26:21,886 --> 00:26:25,556
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Train to New York,
overnight to London, for starts.</font>

198
00:26:26,683 --> 00:26:30,978
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I might end up teaching in Leipzig.
Heinrich owes me a favor.</font>

199
00:26:31,062 --> 00:26:32,438
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'll wire you when I get settled.</font>

200
00:26:32,522 --> 00:26:34,231
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You can send on
the rest of my things.</font>

201
00:26:34,357 --> 00:26:36,483
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I suppose
there's nothing to keep you here.</font>

202
00:26:36,568 --> 00:26:38,527
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I barely recognize
this country anymore.</font>

203
00:26:38,612 --> 00:26:41,697
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The government's got us
seeing Communists in our soup.</font>

204
00:26:41,781 --> 00:26:46,327
<font face="Comic Sans MS">When the hysteria reaches academia,
I guess it's time to call it a career.</font>

205
00:26:46,411 --> 00:26:48,454
<font face="Comic Sans MS">How did Deirdre take the news?</font>

206
00:26:48,538 --> 00:26:50,831
<font face="Comic Sans MS">How does any wife take such things?</font>

207
00:26:50,915 --> 00:26:54,084
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The look on her face was
a combination of pride and panic.</font>

208
00:26:54,169 --> 00:26:57,129
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I never should've doubted you,
my friend.</font>

209
00:26:57,213 --> 00:27:00,966
<font face="Comic Sans MS">No, you have reason to question
your friends these days.</font>

210
00:27:05,555 --> 00:27:08,015
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Brutal couple of years, huh, Charlie?</font>

211
00:27:09,976 --> 00:27:12,686
<font face="Comic Sans MS">First Dad, then Marcus.</font>

212
00:27:13,730 --> 00:27:16,148
<font face="Comic Sans MS">We seem to have reached the age
where life stops giving us things ...</font>

213
00:27:16,232 --> 00:27:18,400
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and starts taking them away.</font>

214
00:27:21,571 --> 00:27:23,739
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Just another half glass.</font>

215
00:28:21,923 --> 00:28:23,132
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Hey!</font>

216
00:28:24,968 --> 00:28:26,468
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Hey, old man!</font>

217
00:28:27,637 --> 00:28:31,682
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Professor, hello! Hey!
Are you Dr. Jones?</font>

218
00:28:31,766 --> 00:28:33,559
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You're running out of platform, kid.</font>

219
00:28:33,643 --> 00:28:35,853
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Are you a friend of Dr. Oxley's?</font>

220
00:28:35,937 --> 00:28:38,313
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Harold Oxley? The archeologist?
- Yeah.</font>

221
00:28:38,398 --> 00:28:39,940
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What about him?</font>

222
00:28:40,984 --> 00:28:42,109
<font face="Comic Sans MS">They're going to kill him.</font>

223
00:28:44,863 --> 00:28:47,865
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I haven't talked to Harold Oxley
in 20 years.</font>

224
00:28:49,242 --> 00:28:51,493
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He's a brilliant guy.</font>

225
00:28:51,578 --> 00:28:54,455
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He could put you to sleep
just by talking.</font>

226
00:28:54,539 --> 00:28:57,624
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Yeah. Yeah. When I was a kid,
that's how I did get to sleep.</font>

227
00:28:57,709 --> 00:29:01,628
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Oxley's voice was better than
a glass of warm milk, you know.</font>

228
00:29:01,713 --> 00:29:03,672
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The name's Mutt, Mutt Williams.</font>

229
00:29:03,757 --> 00:29:06,925
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Mutt? What kind of name is that?
- Yeah.</font>

230
00:29:07,010 --> 00:29:09,052
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It's the one I picked.
You got a problem with it?</font>

231
00:29:09,137 --> 00:29:13,432
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Take it easy.
What was your relationship to Oxley?</font>

232
00:29:13,516 --> 00:29:18,020
<font face="Comic Sans MS">My dad died in the war.
Ox kind of helped my mom raise me.</font>

233
00:29:18,104 --> 00:29:21,064
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You were saying
somebody's going to kill him?</font>

234
00:29:23,735 --> 00:29:27,070
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Six months ago,
my mom gets a letter from the Ox.</font>

235
00:29:27,155 --> 00:29:28,614
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He's down in Peru.</font>

236
00:29:28,698 --> 00:29:31,408
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Found some type of skull,
a crystal skull.</font>

237
00:29:31,493 --> 00:29:35,120
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Like the one that guy
Mitchell-Hodgkiss? Hedgkiss?</font>

238
00:29:35,205 --> 00:29:37,539
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- The one he found.
- Nice jacket.</font>

239
00:29:38,541 --> 00:29:42,961
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The Ox and I were obsessed with
the Mitchell-Hedges skull in college.</font>

240
00:29:43,046 --> 00:29:44,213
<font face="Comic Sans MS">How do you know about it?</font>

241
00:29:44,297 --> 00:29:45,589
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Are you kidding?
It's all he talked about.</font>

242
00:29:45,673 --> 00:29:47,466
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He'd talk about that thing
till the cows come home.</font>

243
00:29:47,550 --> 00:29:49,468
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What's it? It's like an idol?</font>

244
00:29:49,552 --> 00:29:52,346
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Deity carving. Mesoamerican.</font>

245
00:29:52,430 --> 00:29:54,556
<font face="Comic Sans MS">There are a number of crystal skulls
in the world.</font>

246
00:29:54,641 --> 00:29:57,392
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I saw one in the British Museum.</font>

247
00:29:57,727 --> 00:30:01,355
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Interesting craftsmanship,
but that's about it.</font>

248
00:30:01,439 --> 00:30:04,274
<font face="Comic Sans MS">All right, well, laugh if you want.
Oxley said he found it this time.</font>

249
00:30:04,359 --> 00:30:08,320
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He said this was real and he was off
to a place called Akator with it.</font>

250
00:30:08,404 --> 00:30:11,156
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Akator? He said that? You're sure?
- Yeah.</font>

251
00:30:11,241 --> 00:30:14,910
<font face="Comic Sans MS">That's what he said.
He said Akator. What is it?</font>

252
00:30:14,994 --> 00:30:18,622
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It's a mythical lost city
in the Amazon.</font>

253
00:30:18,706 --> 00:30:21,667
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Conquistadors called it El Dorado.</font>

254
00:30:21,751 --> 00:30:25,838
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Supposedly, the Ugha tribe were
chosen by the gods 7,000 years ago ...</font>

255
00:30:25,922 --> 00:30:29,675
<font face="Comic Sans MS">to build a giant city
out of solid gold.</font>

256
00:30:29,759 --> 00:30:32,344
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It had aqueducts and paved roads ...</font>

257
00:30:32,428 --> 00:30:37,516
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and technology that wouldn't
be seen again for 5,000 years.</font>

258
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:42,604
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Francisco de Orellana disappeared
into the Amazon looking for it in 1546.</font>

259
00:30:43,606 --> 00:30:46,608
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I almost died of typhus
looking for it myself.</font>

260
00:30:48,111 --> 00:30:49,486
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I don't think it exists.</font>

261
00:30:49,571 --> 00:30:52,447
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Why would Ox
want to take the skull there?</font>

262
00:30:52,532 --> 00:30:56,368
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The legend says that a crystal
skull was stolen from Akator ...</font>

263
00:30:56,452 --> 00:30:58,370
<font face="Comic Sans MS">in the 15th or 16th century,</font>

264
00:30:58,454 --> 00:31:02,082
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and that whoever returns
the skull to the city temple ...</font>

265
00:31:02,166 --> 00:31:04,376
