266
00:31:04,460 --> 00:31:08,297
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Power. Right. So there's some
kind of power. What's the power?</font>

267
00:31:08,381 --> 00:31:11,466
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I don't know, kid.
It's just a story.</font>

268
00:31:11,551 --> 00:31:12,718
<font face="Comic Sans MS">No.</font>

269
00:31:13,595 --> 00:31:15,721
<font face="Comic Sans MS">From his letter, my mom thought
the Ox was off his rocker.</font>

270
00:31:15,805 --> 00:31:16,847
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You know, smog in the noggin,</font>

271
00:31:16,931 --> 00:31:20,225
<font face="Comic Sans MS">so she goes down there to find him,
only he'd already been kidnapped.</font>

272
00:31:20,310 --> 00:31:22,060
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Now they've got her, too.</font>

273
00:31:22,145 --> 00:31:23,604
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Now, Ox said
he hid that skull someplace,</font>

274
00:31:23,688 --> 00:31:26,940
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and if my mom doesn't come up with it,
they're gonna kill them both.</font>

275
00:31:27,025 --> 00:31:29,151
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Now, she said you'd help me.</font>

276
00:31:29,903 --> 00:31:32,070
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Me? What's your mom's name again?</font>

277
00:31:32,155 --> 00:31:34,907
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Mary. Mary Williams.
You remember her?</font>

278
00:31:34,991 --> 00:31:36,241
<font face="Comic Sans MS">There were a lot of Marys, kid.</font>

279
00:31:36,326 --> 00:31:38,452
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Shut up! That's my mother
you're talking about!</font>

280
00:31:38,536 --> 00:31:40,329
<font face="Comic Sans MS">All right? That's my mother.</font>

281
00:31:40,413 --> 00:31:43,415
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You don't have to get sore all the
time just to prove how tough you are.</font>

282
00:31:43,499 --> 00:31:45,667
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Sit down. Please. Sit down.</font>

283
00:31:47,003 --> 00:31:49,963
<font face="Comic Sans MS">She said if anybody could find
the skull, it's you.</font>

284
00:31:50,048 --> 00:31:54,593
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Like you're some type of ...
Like a grave robber or something.</font>

285
00:31:54,677 --> 00:31:57,512
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'm a tenured professor of archeology.</font>

286
00:31:57,597 --> 00:32:01,850
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Oh, you're a teacher.
Well, that's gonna be a big help.</font>

287
00:32:01,935 --> 00:32:03,936
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Anyway, she called me
2 weeks ago from South America.</font>

288
00:32:04,020 --> 00:32:06,521
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Said she'd escaped,
but they were after her.</font>

289
00:32:06,606 --> 00:32:08,273
<font face="Comic Sans MS">She said she'd just gotten
a letter from the Ox ...</font>

290
00:32:08,358 --> 00:32:10,359
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and mailed it to me
so I could give it to you.</font>

291
00:32:10,443 --> 00:32:11,818
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Then the line went dead.
I opened it.</font>

292
00:32:11,903 --> 00:32:14,363
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I mean, the thing's pointless,
though. It's just gibberish.</font>

293
00:32:14,447 --> 00:32:16,823
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It's not even English lettering.</font>

294
00:32:16,908 --> 00:32:18,075
<font face="Comic Sans MS">See?</font>

295
00:32:19,911 --> 00:32:23,246
<font face="Comic Sans MS">See those two bricks over there,
at the counter?</font>

296
00:32:23,331 --> 00:32:25,916
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I don't think
they're here for the milkshakes.</font>

297
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:27,501
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Who are they?</font>

298
00:32:28,294 --> 00:32:31,213
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Don't know. Maybe FBI.</font>

299
00:32:31,297 --> 00:32:33,048
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Come quietly, Dr. Jones.</font>

300
00:32:33,132 --> 00:32:34,549
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Make that KGB.</font>

301
00:32:34,634 --> 00:32:37,719
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- And bring letter with you.
- Letter? What letter?</font>

302
00:32:37,804 --> 00:32:39,137
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Letter Mr. Williams just give you.</font>

303
00:32:39,222 --> 00:32:41,139
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Me? Do I look like a mailman?</font>

304
00:32:41,224 --> 00:32:42,975
<font face="Comic Sans MS">We don't ask again.
Come now or we'll ...</font>

305
00:32:43,059 --> 00:32:44,226
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Or what?</font>

306
00:32:44,310 --> 00:32:47,562
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Nice try, kid, but I think
you just brought a knife ...</font>

307
00:32:48,898 --> 00:32:51,149
<font face="Comic Sans MS">to a gunfight.</font>

308
00:32:51,234 --> 00:32:52,901
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Outside now.</font>

309
00:32:57,323 --> 00:32:58,490
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Hit this guy.
- Who?</font>

310
00:32:58,574 --> 00:33:00,033
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Joe College. Hit him hard.</font>

311
00:33:00,118 --> 00:33:02,077
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Here, hold this.
- What?</font>

312
00:33:03,079 --> 00:33:04,913
<font face="Comic Sans MS">That's my boyfriend!</font>

313
00:33:08,251 --> 00:33:09,835
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Take it outside!</font>

314
00:33:09,919 --> 00:33:11,753
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Get that greaser!</font>

315
00:33:19,470 --> 00:33:20,887
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Your mom didn't escape.</font>

316
00:33:20,972 --> 00:33:23,765
<font face="Comic Sans MS">They let her go,
so she could mail the letter ...</font>

317
00:33:23,850 --> 00:33:27,102
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and you could bring it to me
and I could translate it!</font>

318
00:33:29,272 --> 00:33:31,106
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Get on, gramps!</font>

319
00:33:59,552 --> 00:34:01,887
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Go, go, go, go, go!</font>

320
00:35:11,624 --> 00:35:24,511
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Better dead than Red!
Better dead than Red!</font>

321
00:35:26,055 --> 00:35:29,558
<font face="Comic Sans MS">This is crazy!
Somebody's going to get hurt!</font>

322
00:35:57,545 --> 00:35:59,212
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Left! Go left! Left!</font>

323
00:36:14,395 --> 00:36:16,188
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Move, move! Move!</font>

324
00:36:16,898 --> 00:36:18,190
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Split, split! Split, split!</font>

325
00:36:18,274 --> 00:36:20,692
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- You're going too fast.
- That's a matter of opinion!</font>

326
00:36:33,831 --> 00:36:36,666
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Excuse me, Dr. Jones.
- Yes?</font>

327
00:36:36,751 --> 00:36:40,086
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I just had a question on
Hargrove's normative culture model.</font>

328
00:36:40,171 --> 00:36:41,546
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Forget Hargrove.</font>

329
00:36:41,631 --> 00:36:44,716
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Read Vere Gordon Childe
on diffusionism.</font>

330
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:46,968
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He spent most of his life
in the field.</font>

331
00:36:47,970 --> 00:36:50,972
<font face="Comic Sans MS">If you want to be
a good archeologist,</font>

332
00:36:52,099 --> 00:36:54,643
<font face="Comic Sans MS">you got to get out of the library!</font>

333
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:00,482
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Who is that?</font>

334
00:37:00,566 --> 00:37:03,693
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Francisco de Orellana,
the conquistador.</font>

335
00:37:03,778 --> 00:37:06,029
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Remember, the guy who got lost
looking for the skull.</font>

336
00:37:06,113 --> 00:37:09,616
<font face="Comic Sans MS">And just as I thought.</font>

337
00:37:09,700 --> 00:37:11,701
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Koihoma.</font>

338
00:37:11,786 --> 00:37:13,245
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What's that?</font>

339
00:37:13,329 --> 00:37:18,333
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It's an extinct Latin American language.
Pre-Columbian syllabic base.</font>

340
00:37:19,585 --> 00:37:23,630
<font face="Comic Sans MS">See. Diagonal stresses on the
ideograms. Definitely Koihoma.</font>

341
00:37:23,714 --> 00:37:25,590
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- You speak it?
- Nobody speaks it.</font>

342
00:37:25,675 --> 00:37:29,010
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It hasn't been heard aloud
in 3,000 years.</font>

343
00:37:29,095 --> 00:37:33,348
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I might be able to read a bit though
if I walk it through Mayan first.</font>

344
00:37:34,183 --> 00:37:36,643
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You know, for an old man,
you ain't bad in a fight.</font>

345
00:37:36,727 --> 00:37:38,478
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Thanks a lot.</font>

346
00:37:38,562 --> 00:37:40,522
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What are you, like, 80?</font>

347
00:37:43,901 --> 00:37:46,069
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It's a riddle.</font>

348
00:37:46,153 --> 00:37:49,698
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Leave it to Ox to write a riddle
in a dead language.</font>

349
00:37:51,200 --> 00:37:55,287
<font face="Comic Sans MS">"Follow the lines in the earth
only gods can read ...</font>

350
00:37:55,371 --> 00:37:58,456
<font face="Comic Sans MS">"which lead to Orellana's cradle ...</font>

351
00:37:58,541 --> 00:38:00,792
<font face="Comic Sans MS">"guarded by the living dead."</font>

352
00:38:00,876 --> 00:38:03,795
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- He's talking about the Nazca Lines.
- What are those?</font>

353
00:38:03,879 --> 00:38:05,213
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Hold on here.</font>

354
00:38:06,007 --> 00:38:12,470
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Geoglyphs. Giant ancient drawings
carved into the desert floor in Peru.</font>

355
00:38:12,555 --> 00:38:15,307
<font face="Comic Sans MS">From the ground,
they don't look like anything.</font>

356
00:38:15,391 --> 00:38:19,019
<font face="Comic Sans MS">But from the sky,
only the gods can read them,</font>

357
00:38:19,103 --> 00:38:21,938
<font face="Comic Sans MS">because only gods live up there.</font>

358
00:38:23,899 --> 00:38:29,154
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Oxley's telling us
the skull is in Nazca, Peru.</font>

359
00:39:30,966 --> 00:39:33,093
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Finally. They saw him.</font>

360
00:39:33,177 --> 00:39:36,054
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Ox wandered into town a couple of
